<a name='argument-355'></a>
<div class='argument' data-id='355'>
<div class='header'>
<a href="http://www.chopshopstore.com"><img alt="Tiny" class="created-by-image" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/electnext/users/photos/23124/tiny." />
</a><div class='header-right'>
<a href="http://www.chopshopstore.com" class="created-by-name">Thomas John Romer</a>
<div class='cred-score'>
85
cred
</div>
</div>
<div class='clear'></div>
<div class='created-at'>Jan 25, 2012</div>
</div>
<div class='argument-text'>
Most people that qualify for the low rate on Capital Gains considered it a gift when it was created and expected it would have been gone long ago. The only thing keeping it at the current rate is the inability for any politician to raise any tax at any time because they all (Democrats included) live in fear of being branded as someone who raises taxes.
</div>
