<div class='divider'></div>
<a name='argument-203'></a>
<div class='argument' data-id='203'>
<div class='header'>
<a href=""><img alt="Unknown-tiny" class="created-by-image" src="/images/unknown-tiny.png?1330528636" />
</a><div class='header-right'>
<a href="" class="created-by-name">Carolyn</a>
<div class='cred-score'>
-35
cred
</div>
</div>
<div class='clear'></div>
<div class='created-at'>Nov 29, 2011</div>
</div>
<div class='argument-text'>
Cutting taxes stimulates consumer spending. Thus, by reducing taxes it would encourage people to go out and buy things which would in turn stimulate the economy. On the other hand, if the government would raise taxes, it would discourage consumer spending, thus crippling the economy even further. A country cannot have a strong economy if there is not a high rate of consumer spending. Therefore, by reducing taxes the government would in the long run help the economy by encouraging consumer spending. 
</div>
